relevant_findings.description: Document details CIA employee's activities in Cuba and Guatemala
relevant_findings.direct_quote: In May 1960 Subject was certified to the State Department in connection with ninety day proposed TDY in Havana, Cuba with JMARC; and in October 1960 she was transferred from Havana to Guatemala.
relevant_findings.significance: Reveals CIA operational movements in Cuba during critical Cold War period

relevant_findings.description: Potential reference to Cuban intelligence interactions
relevant_findings.direct_quote: In November 1960 Security was advised that according to information from 'the Project' (presumably JMARC) Subject had, while in Cuba, allegedly been having affair with 'three people'
relevant_findings.significance: Suggests complex interpersonal dynamics within CIA operations in Cuba
